Introduction

Household: 14CTRaa

This report provides an overview of the air quality in your home, focusing on PM2.5 concentration levels. Descriptive statistics and visualizations will be presented to illustrate the findings. According to the World Health Organization (WHO) air quality guidelines 2021, the 24-hour mean PM2.5 concentration should not exceed 15 g/m3, read https://www.who.int/news-room/feature-stories/detail/what-are-the-who-air-quality-guidelines for more information on WHO air quality guidelines.

The hourly average ambient (outdoor) PM2.5 concentration levels are incorporated into the visualization of PM2.5 air quality in your home. The historical ambient (outdoor) PM2.5 data is sourced from the National Environmental Agencys API, https://api-open.data.gov.sg/v2/real-time/api/pm25.

The data covers the sampling period from 2025-02-18 to 2025-02-25.
